timeline.bodyText:
For the path, use "/node()/c:version" since we know exactly where to find the version. This prevents us from ever getting two values back, which would cause a break.
Also, I recommend moving all of this into a "private boolean canUpdateAmps" method. And only call it inside the catch block here - we don't need to check this unless we get an exception. And in that private method, put everything in a try/catch block, as we don't ever want an exception being thrown by the version-check code. Instead, do something like this:
logger.warn("Could not determine MarkLogic version; cause: " + e.getMessage() + "; will assume that user can update amps and will throw original exception");

